sect1.para:
Groupthink occurs when people collaborate to reach a consensus on a specific subject matter(s). When groupthink occurs within workplace settings, individual creativity and ideas are not recognized. Persons find it easier or less stressful to agree with a group of people, rather than debate specific ideology brought forth by individuals that are a part of the group itself (Cha et al., 
   2020
). Groupthink played a part in Trudy’s colleagues not responding to the dysfunction that they had chosen to not address. In this case, the “group” decided that by not addressing the issue, they avoided becoming a part of the problem.
